caption.text:
[Love is Better Than Hate]

Sometimes we don't realize about what we said to people. How much words could affect someone's life. Words are strong. They empower people in this world. But words could be a weapon. A weapon that could hurt even 'kill' someone. But also, words could be the reason why someone's still alive. We never knew what someone is going through. So watch your mouth! 
Don't be a 'killer' by saying the negative things. There's always beauty in someone if you see them closer. Spread some positivity. Start by the little things you could do. Saying hi, compliment someone's look and their outfit, compliment things people do, tell someone that she is beautiful. The simple things like that could save someone's life in extreme ways. You have to realize that there are so many lonely people around you. Accompany them. Make them realize that there's someone really cares about him/her. And last, make them feel that his existence means something to you. Cheers! Love is much better than Hate!
